<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Channel Death,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Charged In Drowning Death Of Channel Swimmer</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   BOULOGNE-SUR-MER, France (AP) _ A French magistrate charged a
Brazilian woman in connection with the drowning of another woman
who was trying to swim the English Channel.
   Judith Russo, 51, was charged Friday with ``failing to assist a
person in danger.'' She was in the escort boat Tuesday supervising
the swim of Renata Agondi, 20, also of Brazil.
   Ms. Agondi drowned Tuesday night about six miles off the coast
of France during an attempt to swim from Dover across the channel.
   The magistrate concluded that Ms. Agondi was exhausted, which
led to her drowning, and charged that Ms. Russo did not try to
dissuade her from continuing the swim.
   Judicial officials said Ms. Russo was ordered jailed pending the
fixing of bail.
