<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``If I had had this knowledge before it would have killed me.
It's about to kill me now.'' _ Harry Conrad, father of former Army
Sgt. Clyde Lee Conrad, after his son's arrest in West Germany on
charges that he headed an international spy ring.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``Despite this loss, the days of the Mafia are numbered.'' _
U.S. Attorney Samuel A. Alito Jr., after a jury in Newark, N.J.,
cleared 20 reputed mobsters of racketeering charges following a
marathon, 21-month trial.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``I have never been so far away from my family.'' _ A homesick
Nino Betlemidze, a 22-year-old student from Soviet Georgia who is
part of an unprecedented exchange program involving 56 Soviet
students who will spend a year at U.S. colleges without adult
chaperones.
</TEXT>
