<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Caged Boy,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Boy Beaten And Caged, Prosecution Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Charges have been filed against the father
and stepmother of an 8-year-old boy who allegedly was regularly
beaten and confined in a cage until he sought help from a neighbor,
prosecutors say.
   Andrew Ezell Crosby, 34, and Brigettatha Brown, 31, pleaded
innocent Friday to charges of child endangering and causing great
bodily injury, said Andy Reynolds, spokesman for the district
attorney's office.
   They were arrested Aug. 4 after the boy asked a neighbor ``if he
could stay with her for the rest of her life,'' Reynolds said.
   The neighbor called police and the boy was taken to a hospital
where he was found to have been severely abused, he said.
   The parents had posted $13,000 bail each after their initial
arrest. They were taken into custody Friday when their bail was
increased to $75,000.
   The boy was placed in Los Angeles County custody and the
couple's two other children were being cared for by a grandfather,
Reynolds said.
